div.h1: Task State Segment Structure, SS0:ESP0, and GDT Descriptor

p.strong: 104-byte hardware structure Ring 30 privilege transition kernel stack pointer

div.p: The Invariant: TSS.ESP0 Must Equal new_proc->kernel_stack_top BEFORE context_switch_asm() Swaps ESP
Index 0 Selector 0x00 Null Descriptor (required by architecture)
Index 1 Selector 0x08 Kernel Code DPL=0 Base=0 Limit=4GB G=1 D=1
Index 2 Selector 0x10 Kernel Data DPL=0 Base=0 Limit=4GB G=1 D=1
Index 3 Selector 0x1B (RPL=3) User Code DPL=3 Base=0 Limit=4GB G=1 D=1
Index 4 Selector 0x23 (RPL=3) User Data DPL=3 Base=0 Limit=4GB G=1 D=1
Index 5 Selector 0x28 TSS DESCRIPTOR Type=0x89 (32-bit TSS, Available) S=0 (system) DPL=0 P=1 Base = &kernel_tss Limit = 0x67 (103) Granularity=0 (byte granularity)
Byte Layout x86 Hardware-Mandated Format All offsets are fixed by architecture (IA-32 SDM Vol. 3, 7.2.1)
Offset 0x00 prev_tss (uint32_t) Link to previous TSS hardware task switch chain Always 0x00000000 for software task switching
Offset 0x04 esp0 (uint32_t) CRITICAL FIELD Ring 0 (kernel) stack pointer. CPU reads this on 30 transition. MUST be updated on every context switch.
Offset 0x08 ss0 (uint32_t) CRITICAL FIELD Ring 0 (kernel) stack segment selector. Fixed: 0x00000010 (GDT entry 2 = kernel data)
0x0C0x17 esp1, ss1, esp2, ss2 Ring 1/2 stacks unused on Linux/modern kernels. All zeros
Offset 0x1C cr3 (uint32_t) Page directory for hardware task switch unused.
0x200x5B GPR Snapshot eax, ecx, edx, ebx, esp, ebp, esi, edi, etc. All zeros (software task switching uses stack)
0x5C0x6B Segment Snapshot es, cs, ss, ds, fs, gs, ldt All zeros
Offset 0x64 trap (uint16_t) Trap on task switch bit 0x0000
Offset 0x66 iomap_base (uint16_t) I/O permission bitmap offset. 0x0068 = sizeof(tss_t) (bitmap empty)

Bytes 74 (High Dword) 31 24 23 22 21 20 19 16 15 14 13 12 11 8 7 0
